      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="662-35AD" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">To the Author of the L<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">ONDON</hi> D<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">AILY</hi> P<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">OST</hi>.</l></lg><lg n="2" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-1-line-group-2" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-1-line-group-2-line-1"><hi rend="underline">SIR</hi>,</l></lg><lg n="3" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-1-line-group-3" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-1-line-group-3-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">T</hi>HERE being no Mail, I fancy the Two following pieces of Dean Swift's, will be an agreeable Entertainment to your Readers; they are from the late Dublin Edition of his Works, so but in few Hands as yet.</l></lg><lg n="4" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-1-line-group-4" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-1-line-group-4-line-1">Yours,</l></lg><lg n="5" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-1-line-group-5" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-1-line-group-5-line-1"><note rend="flush right">A. B.</note></l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1">Written in the Year 1733.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1">By Dean S<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">WIFT</hi>.</l></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">P</hi>OOR Ladies! though their Bus'ness be to play,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-line-2"> 'Tis hard they must be busy Night and Day:</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-line-3"> Why should they want the Privilege of Men,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-line-4"> Nor take some small Diversions now and then?</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-line-5"> Had Women been the Makers of our Laws;</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-line-6"> (And why they were not, I can see no Cause;)</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-line-7"> The Men should slave at Cards from Morn to Night;</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-662-35AD-line-8"> And Female Pleasures be to read and write.662-35AD   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
